text: Their pulut serunding ($2) was nice, sweeter than the ones I had in KL, but no less complex and well balanced. Super friendly locals around! I was recommended the chee cheong fun here by a friendly uncle. Will go try next time!

Wide variety of Nyonya food fares.
The food quality is not fantastic, but the prices are wallet friendly. Fried bee hoon clears out fast, each patron buying 3 to 4 packets.
Do note it draws a long queue in the morning, so you can expect to wait about 10-15 minutes before being served.

The cheapest and decent food in this area. Noodle + Egg + Luncheon Meat + Tao Kee + Ice Soya Milk only cost S$3.30. They have other things like chui kueu, bak zhang, and many other kueh and food. Highly Recommended to patronise.

Get to know this place because the MP who is speaker of Singapore parliament always visited here for breakfast.

Purposely bought their kueh to try. In Bedok, you can find a few kueh manufacturers but here is the one that price cheap and nice taste.

Basically I can't pick any mistake in their kueh. Recommend to come again.
Old folks friendly, wide variety of food and should try their tradition fried mee or been hoon ,go without any sides ,taste nice too with the sauce.
